abstract: Boeing said that its third-quarter net income dropped 38 percent because of a strike by machinists and supplier-related issues.
snippet: Boeing said that its third-quarter net income dropped 38 percent because of a strike by machinists and supplier-related issues.
lead_paragraph: The Boeing Company, which was struck seven weeks ago by the union representing its machinists, said Wednesday that its third-quarter net income dropped 38 percent because of the strike and other production issues.

headline.main: Earnings Drop 38% at Boeing as a Machinists’ Strike Wears On
headline.print_headline: Earnings Drop 38% at Boeing as a Machinists’ Strike Wears On
